sertj_core/ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerUsingUnsafeInjectionTest.java`\n\nWhat was refined:\n\n- Added an external attach helper process instead of self-attach, because `jdk.attach.allowAttachSelf` is not reliable when set after JVM startup.\n- Added a small Java agent generated at test runtime to open the JDK packages needed by AssertJ 3.22.0’s bundled legacy Byte Buddy reflection/unsafe injection path:\n  - `java.lang`\n  - `java.lang.reflect`\n  - `jdk.internal.misc`\n  - `sun.misc`\n- Restored targeted Byte Buddy class-injection scenarios after package opens:\n  - generated type definition\n  - package definition\n  - package fallback path after concurrent package definition\n- Kept the public AssertJ soft-assertions proxy scenario.\n- Kept Native Image unsupported-feature handling.\n- Added bounded external process wait.\n\nI did not run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0`.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_079fc6a7bc1ecf8e016a25f79a4a0c81909be7589f040b0557\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1410, "output": 863, "cacheRead": 91136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 93409, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780873096813, "responseId": "resp_079fc6a7bc1ecf8e016a25f789c6fc8190882ca7d9b015d562"}}
